{
  "texts": [
    "Half of those who have a heart attack are not 'at risk'.",
    "These concerns require automatic prediction of heart disease and earlier identification, which is a critical issue.",
    "It is essential to prevent this life-threatening disease before it leads to millions of deaths.",
    "It is important to identify various risk factors to diagnose and prevent this disease earlier, such as Coronary Artery Disease (CAD), Diabetes, Hypertension, Hyperlipidemia, Smoking, Medications, Family history of CAD, and Obesity [6][7][8][9].All other heart risk factors must be identified with indicators and temporal features, except CAD in the family and smoking status.",
    "Each characteristic of the indicator indicates the clinical significance of the risk factor."
  ]
}